runs.screened_message: We thank you for your time spent taking this questionnaire. Your results have been recorded.

children.label: b29211055
children.text: This survey is for gathering information on kneecap pain in the population of people aged between 18 to 40 years old. In England, a separate consent form is not required for questionnaires - a consent is implied by the return of the questionnaire. If you are happy to proceed, please select 'Yes' below.

children.label: b29209907
children.text: What is your sex?

children.label: b29938463
children.text: How old are you?

children.label: b29213588
children.text: Have you ever been to a doctor because of knee problems?

children.label: b29213615
children.text: Have you had pain or problems in the last year in or around the knee?

children.label: b29213685
children.text: In which knee have you had pain or problems?

children.label: b29213855
children.text: Have you had surgery to your knee? (Including arthroscopy, keyhole surgery, camera in your knee)

children.label: b29213869
children.text: Have you ever had a kneecap that has gone out of joint (dislocated)?

children.label: b29214047
children.text: Since starting with your knee problem, does your knee ever swell up?

children.label: b29214421
children.text: Have you had pain and discomfort for more than one month?

children.label: b29214458
children.text: Because of your knee problems would you suffer from pain or difficulty with sitting for a long time?

children.label: b29214475
children.text: Because of your knee problems would you suffer from pain or difficulty with going up stairs?

children.label: b29214528
children.text: Because of your knee problems would you suffer from pain or difficulty with going downstairs?

children.label: b29214555
children.text: Because of your knee problems would you suffer from pain or difficulty with squatting?

children.label: b29214640
children.text: Because of your knee problems would you suffer from pain or difficulty with standing for long periods?

children.label: b29214686
children.text: Because of your knee problems would you suffer from pain or difficulty with walking on a level surface?

children.label: b29214692
children.text: Because of your knee problems would you suffer from pain or difficulty with getting up out of a chair?

children.label: b29214696
children.text: Because of your knee problems would you suffer from pain or difficulty with kneeling?

children.label: b29214699
children.text: Because of your knee problems would you suffer from pain or difficulty with walking on uneven surfaces?

children.label: b29214735
children.text: Because of your knee problems would you suffer from pain or difficulty with walking down slopes?

children.label: b29215014
children.text: Because of your knee problems would you suffer from pain or difficulty with walking up slopes?

children.label: b29215025
children.text: Because of your knee problems would you suffer from pain or difficulty with hopping?

children.label: b29215202
children.text: Because of your knee problems would you suffer from pain or difficulty with jumping?

children.label: b29215203
children.text: Because of your knee problems would you suffer from pain or difficulty with running?

children.label: b29247057
children.text: We are now going to ask you some questions about each knee. Starting with your right knee.

children.label: b29215314
children.text: Thinking about your right knee, what do you consider is your main problem with your knee?

options.text: Giving way or feeling like it will give way

children.label: b29215379
children.text: Thinking about your right knee, did your current knee problem come on.

options.text: Because of a sudden injury e.g. twist, fall or accident that you needed to see a doctor about
Gradually over a period of time
Neither gradually nor because of a sudden injury

children.label: b29247115
children.text: We are now going to ask you some questions about each knee. Starting with your left knee.

children.label: b29215446
children.text: Thinking about your left knee, what do you consider your main problem with your knee?

options.text: Giving way or feeling like it will give way

children.label: b29215514
children.text: Thinking about your left knee, did your current knee problem come on

options.text: Because of a sudden injury e.g. twist, fall or accident that you needed to see a doctor about
Gradually over a period of time
Neither gradually nor because of a sudden injury

children.label: b29172228
children.text: We would like you to imagine that this is a picture of your knees. Please select the number that corresponds to your area of knee pain. You can select more than one number. (With options to select numbers 1 to 8).

children.label: b29259365
children.text: If you feel pain in the back of your knee, please select the box that corresponds to the knee you are experiencing the pain.

children.label: b29216269
children.text: Considering both your knees which would you say is the knee that gives you most problems? ​

children.label: b32185483
children.text: Please click the button below to finish the survey.

children.label: b32185902
children.text: We thank you for your time spent taking this questionnaire. Your results have been recorded.
